  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dbb\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2: \u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dba\u0ddd \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "PM Ranil should resign: Party leaders say",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is said from parliamentary sources that the majority of party leaders have indicated to the speaker at the parliamentary affairs committee meeting that Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe should resign from his position immediately in order to resolve the crisis in the country.",
        "The party leaders have also stated that the Speaker should be appointed as the Acting President after handing over the letter of resignation of the President.",
        "The Committee on Parliamentary Affairs met today (13) afternoon at the Parliament complex under the chairmanship of Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena.",
        "The Speaker, Mr. Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena, who has commented here, has stated that after the President has submitted his resignation letter, Parliament will be convened and necessary measures will be taken to appoint a new President.",
        "The Chief of Defense Staff General Shavendra Silva, the three armed forces commanders and the Inspector General of Police also participated in this meeting.",
        "It was also discussed about the strugglers entering different places. It has been learned that the commanders of the three armed forces have been asked about how to control the militants and the party leaders have requested the commanders of the three armed forces to never use live ammunition for that purpose.",
        "No specific decisions were taken in this meeting and the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs has decided to meet again tomorrow (14) to further discuss the current situation."
      ],
